  <dsc><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_61a3de5a25a4e65d54be482b7fe4b38e" level="item"><did><unittitle>Mademoiselle A. Castens promotional card</unittitle><unitdate certainty="Circa" datechar="creation" normal="1910/1910">1910</unitdate><container id="aspace_eb65f1152cd0637b419d22745b0bc124" label="Mixed Materials [31924131867958]" type="manuscript box">86 - Folder 1</container></did><odd audience="internal" id="aspace_593e87902fa141c42d834c3d599f90a2"><head>General</head><p>Ephemera</p></odd><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_459c3bbf5abdabdd7958919d69ead671"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Promotional card for the fitness practice of Mademoiselle A. Castens, a pioneer in offering physical training for women and children whose salon was located on the swanky boulevard Haussmann. The reference to "réspiration normale" no doubt represents pushback against the fashion of tight corsets for women, which were increasingly seen as a threat to health. The card features high-style fine-press art nouveau typography and decorative graphics by Graveur Stern, a leading society engraver and printer in business in the Passage des Panoramas in Paris from 1834 to 2015.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_b5310e51395b23b671ec4012e240141f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Body Builder</unittitle><unitdate certainty="Circa" datechar="creation" normal="1905/1905">1905</unitdate><container id="aspace_51413e6303390d62d937ee3847d4eff7" label="Mixed Materials [31924131867958]" type="manuscript box">86 - Folder 1</container></did><odd audience="internal" id="aspace_306ba8051c4fdb3bdacd0aac0e88e016"><head>General</head><p>Postcard</p></odd><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_c1b63d82d9b6399d2fb07cf8736c414a"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Produced by Atelier Mercép, a popular portrait studio in the capital of Croatia.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_6c763626c88f2fe5f9566789a66dcc2d" level="item"><did><unittitle>Graphic for the "Esposizione delle Industrie e del Lavoro"</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1911/1911">1911</unitdate><container id="aspace_f25c68ee7a06c3f934a39979e74d866b" label="Mixed Materials [31924131867958]" type="manuscript box">86 - Folder 1</container></did><odd audience="internal" id="aspace_6d4866e8f341758cc5db122e3b4289d5"><head>General</head><p>Postcard</p></odd><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_d007b98f155c2e98a10949b1b61a930a"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Turin: Edizione della Commisione Esecutiva per L'Esposizione Internationale di Torino; designed by Italian artist Adolfo De Carolis</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_cc7c85399479888cdf5356459f7973ea" level="item"><did><unittitle>"Marathon"</unittitle><unitdate certainty="Circa" datechar="creation" normal="1910/1910">1910</unitdate><container id="aspace_63b7c115dab6d0a8ceb79c829d06aa87" label="Mixed Materials [31924131867958]" type="manuscript box">86 - Folder 1</container></did><odd audience="internal" id="aspace_5616b03dd0ff2a6949b3ca5962edcc26"><head>General</head><p>Postcard</p></odd><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_48d000e677b3242a07931997c60636e1"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Period reproduction of a painting by Czech artist Josef Kočí.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_79fd7ccb859abe27488b41bd64cf959c" level="item"><did><unittitle>"Sportschulung"</unittitle><unitdate certainty="Circa" datechar="creation" normal="1925/1925">1925</unitdate><container id="aspace_178f52e2f85d89aaa45acc1328b114de" label="Mixed Materials [31924131867958]" type="manuscript box">86 - Folder 1</container></did><odd audience="internal" id="aspace_b1c53592b1261b7a9cab2b4a67ef354e"><head>General</head><p>Postcard</p></odd><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_ddc000c442cd8dd4053e4abba764d3b6"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Image of German fitness guru Hans Surén (1885–1972), published by the nudist magazine "Schönheit"